SQL 

1.	Data Query language(DQL) / Data Retrieval Language(DRL) :  select

2.	Data Manipulation Language(DML) : insert, update, delete, merge

3.	Data Definition Language(DDL) : create, drop, rename, alter, truncate

4.	Transaction Control Language(TCL) : commit, rollback, save

5.	Data Control Language(DCL) : grant, revoke


PL/SQL

1.	Stored Procedure

2.	User Defined Function

3.	Packages

4.	Triggers


CONNECTING WITH ORACLE DATABASE 

1.	Go to commandprompt

2.	sql> sqlplus

3.	enter username: scott (not case sensitive)

4.	enter password: tiger (case sensitive)

ORACLE 11G 

-> Managing of information (reading,adding,modify,deleting)

-> using a language SQL

-> Application are not limited

-> coding is simple
